WEBVTT

00:00.002 --> 00:05.949
I want you to notice in the Scriptures tonight, as we consider, where are we going as a church family?

00:05.969 --> 00:11.976
Let me share with you the biblical basis as we saw this morning in the Word of God.

00:12.817 --> 00:19.906
In Philippians chapter 3, verse 13, we hear the testimony of the apostle Paul, and I was speaking this afternoon.

00:19.986 --> 00:26.994
We had the opportunity to have lunch with our county supervisor, Catherine Barger and the mayor of Palmdale and some other guests.

00:27.074 --> 00:47.986
And I was sharing with them one of the things that I so enjoy about studying the churches of Northern Macedonia in consideration of the church at Philippi in particular is that while they were in a time of impoverishment and while they were under Roman pressure and difficulty,

00:48.162 --> 00:50.846
they still became model churches.

00:50.926 --> 00:56.334
When you say Thessalonica, when you say Philippi, you think of soul winning churches and giving churches.

00:56.714 --> 01:02.022
And I'm gonna tell you something, it doesn't matter where you're located, the gospel is not bound.

01:02.082 --> 01:04.525
And the power of the gospel is not bound.

01:04.585 --> 01:10.353
And I believe that God receives much glory from a church that is seeking to do His will His way.

01:10.373 --> 01:11.876
And this is what happened.

01:11.976 --> 01:16.402
God, as we saw this morning, took a businesswoman, a jailer,

01:16.546 --> 01:24.277
and a formerly demon-possessed girl, and he made them into something we call a church, a called-out assembly of believers.

01:24.557 --> 01:25.719
Isn't the gospel wonderful?

01:26.379 --> 01:27.561
That's what God can do.

01:28.102 --> 01:33.069
And so Paul is writing to the church of Philippi, and he's sharing his testimony with them.

01:33.129 --> 01:42.962
And in verse 13, we learned this morning these words, brethren, I count not myself to have apprehended, but this one thing I do.

01:43.490 --> 01:49.537
Now here we saw in the first place the humility of the apostle, I've not arrived.

01:49.557 --> 01:52.020
How many of you could say with me, I've not arrived?

01:52.821 --> 01:53.922
I need to grow this year.

01:54.322 --> 01:56.845
He said, I've not apprehended, but this one thing I do.

01:56.865 --> 02:04.294
And there we saw the second principle of focus, focusing on the Lord, this one thing I do.

02:04.694 --> 02:11.602
And here's how he phrases it under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit, forgetting those things which are behind

02:12.098 --> 02:20.832
And reaching forth under those things which are before, I press toward the mark for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ Jesus.

02:21.614 --> 02:24.218
Now, 2019 is behind us.

02:24.238 --> 02:26.722
2020 is before us.

02:27.403 --> 02:32.351
What should our attitude as a church be toward this new year and this new decade?

02:32.812 --> 02:36.498
And I believe it can be summed up in these words, reaching forth.

02:36.834 --> 02:42.789
Many churches are putting their program into neutral and many Christians are even going backward.

02:43.110 --> 02:47.762
But God says as you're looking to see me someday, you ought to be reaching forth.

02:47.938 --> 02:54.046
to see what I have for your life, reaching forth until that day when you see me again.

02:54.066 --> 03:05.081
And so tonight the vision is with that biblical backdrop that we want to be a church that is reaching forth in California in 2020 for the glory of God.

03:05.141 --> 03:07.765
And so let's pray and we'll share this vision tonight.

03:07.905 --> 03:17.458
Father, I know it's just the time and the service where we share the vision, but I don't want to share it without prayer and seeking your face one more time.

03:18.306 --> 03:23.693
Now, Lord, you know the many hours of prayer and study that have gone into this very day.

03:23.753 --> 03:26.256
You know the many hours by our tech teams.

03:26.376 --> 03:33.566
And we thank you, Lord, for the beautiful materials and the various tools that have been given to us today, the calendars.

03:33.666 --> 03:37.991
And we thank you, Lord, for the way our hearts have been encouraged and ministered to.

03:38.051 --> 03:46.482
And yet in this moment, we pray that you would use what I'm about to say to help our church as we reach forth

03:46.658 --> 04:01.714
into the future into this new year Lord may we have you in our hearts mind may you be the mark for which we strive the goal for which we live and may everything that is said and done bring honor and glory to your name tonight I pray

04:01.762 --> 04:03.924
In Jesus' name, amen.

04:03.964 --> 04:04.745
You can be seated.

04:05.105 --> 04:08.128
Well, by now, most of you should have received our presentation folio here.

04:08.148 --> 04:10.770
I'd like you to take that, if you would, into your hands.

04:10.810 --> 04:16.435
And of course, I'm gonna encourage you to read the whole thing with much more detail over the next upcoming days.

04:16.475 --> 04:21.119
But I want to share with you tonight our Reaching Forth 2020 vision.

04:21.579 --> 04:25.322
And you'll notice there's a cover page there, and I'll not read the entire opening letter.

04:25.883 --> 04:31.748
But I will say at the last part of this paragraph I mentioned, it is my prayer that we will reach

04:31.728 --> 04:37.014
as a church family in faith as we follow God's direction together.

04:37.054 --> 04:40.718
That's always been my heart striving together for the faith of the gospel.

04:40.798 --> 04:53.752
That's our goal and you cannot strive in the sense of working together as a team unless all of us are yielded to the Holy Spirit and all of us are seeking to move forward together.

04:53.872 --> 04:56.174
Together everyone achieves more.

04:56.575 --> 05:01.700
Now over the last few months we've been kind of refining and redefining some

05:01.680 --> 05:02.882
of our purpose.

05:03.183 --> 05:11.059
We've given some of our core values and we've talked a little bit about the DNA of Lancaster Baptist and we'll be preaching along the lines of some of these themes.

05:11.099 --> 05:15.027
But I want you to notice on the next page the purpose of Lancaster Baptist.

05:15.067 --> 05:16.490
This certainly is not new.

05:16.530 --> 05:18.353
This has been in place for many, many years.

05:18.414 --> 05:22.642
But we want to bear in mind there are three great themes that we have.

05:22.722 --> 05:24.746
as a church and in our ministry.

05:25.027 --> 05:27.692
The first is to love God fervently.

05:28.093 --> 05:31.119
The second is to grow together biblically.

05:31.179 --> 05:34.646
And the third is to reach others passionately.

05:35.067 --> 05:39.636
These are the three aspects of the purpose of Lancaster Baptist Church.

05:39.656 --> 05:40.477
Let's say those together.

05:40.517 --> 05:42.802
They're fairly simple.

05:42.882 --> 05:44.543
Love God fervently.

05:44.583 --> 05:48.066
Number two, we want to grow together biblically.

05:48.347 --> 05:51.409
And number three, we want to reach others passionately.

05:51.790 --> 06:00.277
Now loving God fervently, that takes place in our worship services and our own personal worship, our time with the Lord growing together biblically.

06:00.317 --> 06:05.001
That happens in our Bible studies, in our connection groups, of course, reaching others passionately.

06:05.261 --> 06:11.967
That happens through our organized soul winning and our personal lives around the valley carrying gospel tracks and being a witness for Christ.

06:12.047 --> 06:12.868
And this is why

06:12.848 --> 06:21.053
exist and this is something that we want to remember as we help new members coming along into the purpose of Lancaster Baptist Church.

06:21.073 --> 06:26.930
We also shared a few weeks ago the core values, some things that the pastoral staff took time and

06:27.298 --> 06:34.264
I took much time just really developing scripturally what are the core values of Lancaster Baptist Church.

06:34.324 --> 06:44.793
Further defining some of our DNA as a church and how can we define, for example, to a visitor, to someone that's looking to Lancaster Baptist as a potential home.

06:44.853 --> 06:46.755
What kind of a church this is.

06:47.115 --> 06:52.300
And we have five that we have placed on the walls in the West Wing lobby and that we're gonna share with you tonight.

06:52.600 --> 06:55.543
I'll be preaching these as well later on in the spring.

06:55.823 --> 06:57.284
The first one simply stated

06:57.264 --> 06:59.828
us, we center all we do on Christ.

07:00.128 --> 07:10.504
We want Jesus Christ to be exalted in every activity, in every service at Lancaster Baptist Church, and that he would have the preeminence is our desire.

07:10.745 --> 07:11.806
This is his church.

07:11.906 --> 07:13.409
It's not our church.

07:13.429 --> 07:14.911
This is the Lord's church.

07:14.931 --> 07:18.957
And we want him to be preeminent in every single service.

07:18.977 --> 07:22.162
Secondly, we want to be a church that submits

07:22.242 --> 07:24.265
to the Word of God.

07:24.526 --> 07:29.554
We believe the Word of God is our final authority, and it's been given by inspiration of God.

07:29.975 --> 07:35.424
And it's been given as to be profitable for doctrine, for correction, for instruction in righteousness.

07:35.444 --> 07:39.791
How many of you are thankful that whenever we come to this place, we know the Bible is going to be open?

07:39.851 --> 07:42.836
Someone's going to stand up and say, open your Bibles too.

07:42.896 --> 07:44.178
How many of you are thankful for that?

07:44.610 --> 07:47.255
How many of you know there are churches where that statement's not heard?

07:47.296 --> 07:51.544
And so I'm thankful that we can continue to be a Bible preaching church.

07:51.584 --> 07:55.994
And we want to have a heart this year, a new and a fresh of Lord speak to me.

07:56.014 --> 07:58.098
I want to follow your word.

07:58.146 --> 08:07.734
The third core value, or value that we would share as we have new members in the new members class, the core class and so forth, is that we engage people with the gospel.

08:07.894 --> 08:11.998
We are a church that is engaging people with the gospel.

08:12.378 --> 08:16.562
Now I can say that from this pulpit, but if we're not doing it, we're not that kind of a church.

08:16.922 --> 08:25.049
And so we want to be challenged tonight to be a people that carry gospel tracks, that attend soul winning opportunities, that share the gospel.

08:25.470 --> 08:28.132
This is why God gives us relationship,

08:28.112 --> 08:32.837
we might be able to tell others what Jesus Christ has done for us.

08:33.137 --> 08:37.582
Number four, we are a church that enjoys serving Jesus.

08:37.662 --> 08:50.636
Now, this is something the Lord put on my heart as I thought, well you know our church is 34 years old now and we've been through some wonderful years and yet we're getting a little bit older but we don't want to lose that joy of serving the Lord.

08:50.656 --> 08:54.881
We've got some new activities this year and some just special things we've never done before.

08:55.481 --> 08:58.084
We want to just keep the spontaneity and the joy

08:58.064 --> 09:08.335
and the fun, if you will, right in the middle of it all, because Jesus said that in the world you'll have tribulation, but be of good cheer for I've overcome the world.

09:08.375 --> 09:10.237
And I'm thankful tonight we're on the winning side.

09:10.617 --> 09:14.782
And I really believe we need to live that way and we're excited that this is a fourth core value.

09:15.002 --> 09:28.036
We're going to be looking for ways either to balance the busy schedule from time to time or to encourage hearts in special ways and to have fun and encouraging services along with exciting times of fellowship at Lancaster.

09:28.016 --> 09:31.834
We make no apology for engaging people with the gospel.

09:32.075 --> 09:34.386
We make no apology for having a revival meeting.

09:35.746 --> 09:38.068
Many churches have given up on revival meetings.

09:38.088 --> 09:42.492
They think no one wants to go to church on a nighttime service, much less two night times in a row.

09:42.512 --> 09:52.260
We don't apologize for having some special emphasis like that, but by the same token, we want to have some times where we can have some rest or fellowship as well along the way.

09:52.300 --> 09:53.521
We want to enjoy serving the Lord.

09:53.541 --> 09:58.466
And then finally, we are a church that believes in living by faith.

09:58.486 --> 10:05.732
We're still believing God to do great and mighty things, whether that is helping us to increase in our missions activity or our busman

10:05.712 --> 10:08.095
or the kid city building or whatever it is.

10:08.375 --> 10:17.304
We're not a church and you'll see this in just a moment sitting on our laurels and so we value the faith life for without faith it's impossible to please him.

10:17.324 --> 10:29.678
And these are some of the values that we want to keep in mind as we move forward and we've placed them as I said on the walls of the West Lobby just to kind of be a reminder to us and to challenge us along the way through our course of ministry.

10:30.058 --> 10:35.684
Then the third area I want to mention just by way of review tonight I preached all of this this past fall but I want to just

10:35.664 --> 10:42.892
We just mentioned our ministry path and Brother Larry Chap will preach this message for us and just kind of reminded us about where we're heading.

10:42.912 --> 10:45.535
And you might say, well, why are you sharing this with us?

10:45.615 --> 10:52.062
Well, first of all, it's a reminder to us with respect to where we want to be growing and how we want to be growing.

10:52.502 --> 11:05.636
But I'm sharing this with you tonight because as you attend maybe one of the connection groups, or as you're a part of one of the ministries, choir, usher, something like this, these are some of the stepways along the path of

11:05.616 --> 11:11.843
Christian maturity that we're trying to help people learn to walk this way in their Christian life.

11:11.883 --> 11:14.426
And so I want you to familiarize yourself with it.

11:14.446 --> 11:15.828
We want to be walking this way.

11:15.888 --> 11:18.071
We want to be helping others walk this way as well.

11:18.471 --> 11:26.541
And we've mentioned these over the years by different terms, but here's the five terms for our ministry path that I want you to remember and help walk others through.

11:26.621 --> 11:31.186
Number one, the first step on the ministry path is the step

11:31.234 --> 11:32.335
of worship.

11:32.655 --> 11:35.257
The step of worship, that's the entry point.

11:35.278 --> 11:40.842
That's when people come in and we have that opportunity to engage them in worship for the Lord Jesus Christ.

11:41.143 --> 11:46.828
We used to say years ago we had all eyes, and the first eye was to inspire people to have a heart for God.

11:47.268 --> 11:59.579
It's our goal that people would come into Lancaster Baptist Church, and yes, even by watching us worship, even by seeing that we love the Lord, that we sing from our hearts, that we say amen to the preaching.

11:59.619 --> 12:01.220
We can practice that right now.

12:01.200 --> 12:11.039
that we're responsive, that we are worshiping God, that we are truly welcoming His presence with us, that people will see whether they're saved or not.

12:11.380 --> 12:14.105
These people are serious about their God.

12:14.646 --> 12:17.892
They are serious about God working in their hearts.

12:18.714 --> 12:20.818
One of the guests I had this morning drove here

12:21.282 --> 12:25.247
from Pasadena and he was sharing with me this afternoon.

12:25.327 --> 12:28.011
He said, you know, I want to come back up here next Sunday.

12:28.031 --> 12:32.036
He said, I've never experienced a time like that in a church.

12:32.277 --> 12:51.282
And, you know, that ought to be our prayer that people who come to Lancaster Baptist Church, that that first step coming into worship, they're not going to see us distracted or talking about football or this or that, but they're going to see us fully engaged in worshiping God and that it will be attractive to them that they'll say, you know what, those people have something I don't have.

12:52.098 --> 12:53.163
And that's the first step.

12:53.344 --> 12:58.450
And if, listen, if visitors come in and they see us kind of, you know, checked out,

12:58.850 --> 13:02.954
spiritually and emotionally and not really involved and not listening and not singing.

13:03.274 --> 13:07.938
Listen, why would they come back if we don't seem to be engaged in worshiping our God?

13:07.958 --> 13:15.324
So the first step is that we want to be a church that loves preaching and loves singing and loves and has a passion for revival.

13:15.685 --> 13:20.849
Now the second step for that visitor that comes is what we're calling community.

13:21.430 --> 13:26.974
We want to see them become a part of our church in the sense of community life.

13:27.074 --> 13:28.836
Now I won't take a lot of time

13:28.816 --> 13:44.691
this, but so many people today in the social media era, while they feel like they have a like and they have a relationship and they have friends on Facebook, the truth is that anxiety and depression and loneliness are on the rise in America today.

13:46.793 --> 13:51.397
And people are starving for community and especially spiritual community.

13:52.418 --> 13:52.838
You know what?

13:52.858 --> 13:56.882
There are people all over the valley that need to know about your connection group.

13:57.666 --> 13:59.890
They need to come from a time of worship.

14:00.194 --> 14:14.386
They need us to go out into their home and maybe send them an email and get ahold of them and say, hey, we'd like to invite you to a group of 12 or 20 or a class of 80, a place where you can find some friends, a place where you can begin to understand the Christian life.

14:14.667 --> 14:16.368
And that's the second part of the path.

14:16.588 --> 14:20.351
And I need all of you this year to help people get on that path.

14:20.452 --> 14:30.180
And yes, we're inviting people to church, but we want to be conscious of those visitors, not just getting into our comfort zone, but finding people that are new to God or just

14:30.626 --> 14:38.333
trying to discover who God is and encourage them to take that second step to become a part of a loving community.

14:38.593 --> 14:42.516
And then thirdly, we want to encourage them to then make a commitment.

14:42.556 --> 14:46.480
Now that commitment, first and foremost, we want to make sure they're saved, amen.

14:46.520 --> 15:00.612
We want to make sure that if they weren't saved in the worship time, if they weren't saved in the visiting of your class and the interaction in the home, that then they're coming to that place where they accept Jesus Christ as their savior and then become involved

15:00.592 --> 15:01.853
in discipleship.

15:02.274 --> 15:13.246
And the continued discipleship is where folks can make that deep commitment, understanding the doctrine, understanding what the church is about, understanding what prayer is about.

15:13.686 --> 15:18.551
And then the fourth step on this ministry path is what we call service.

15:18.591 --> 15:21.594
That's when someone's been saved, they've been discipled.

15:22.095 --> 15:26.440
They're now a part of your community, your class, whatever the case might be.

15:26.760 --> 15:28.962
And maybe they wanna start singing in the choir.

15:29.002 --> 15:30.564
Maybe they are ready to be enough

15:30.544 --> 15:33.607
Maybe they would like to help on a bus route.

15:33.627 --> 15:34.628
And that's wonderful.

15:34.668 --> 15:40.354
That's the natural process of spiritual growth, discovering their gifts and getting on board.

15:40.375 --> 15:51.687
And then, of course, number five, we want to encourage every faithful member of our church to be a part of outreach, telling someone else about the time of worship so that they can come on the ministry path.

15:51.707 --> 15:57.773
And our job is to be walking that path, but also bringing others along the path with us.

15:57.833 --> 16:00.516
And there you have our church purpose.

16:00.496 --> 16:03.019
loving God, growing together, serving others.

16:03.059 --> 16:19.140
You have some core values that we want to live out and that we want to teach to our new members, sinning all we do around Christ, submitting to the Word of God, engaging others with the gospel, enjoying the ministry, living by faith.

16:19.160 --> 16:26.450
And as folks begin to understand that, we want them to journey with us, to journey along the ministry path, worship,

16:26.626 --> 16:32.655
community, commitment, service and outreach, bringing people along the way.

16:32.915 --> 16:45.353
And I hope that you as leaders in this church, teachers and faithful members, that you will take these steps and say, Lord, help me this year to bring somebody else along the path.

16:45.373 --> 16:54.866
How many of you adults tonight and teenagers would like to see even one person that would come into the worship service of this church that you invited?

16:55.362 --> 17:01.522
Somebody that would say to you this year, you know, something was happening in my heart during that service.

17:02.082 --> 17:04.724
Somebody that would say, I'd like to learn more.

17:04.965 --> 17:09.448
And maybe you could invite them to come and enjoy the community of your connection group.

17:09.468 --> 17:10.890
Somebody that would sit with you.

17:11.070 --> 17:14.653
Somebody that you're helping along the ministry path.

17:14.713 --> 17:20.018
And maybe that's somebody that you're able to see saved or their life rededicated.

17:20.078 --> 17:21.419
And you can encourage them.

17:21.439 --> 17:23.140
There's something called discipleship.

17:23.180 --> 17:25.202
And I can take you through it.

17:25.222 --> 17:27.884
Or I know who can take you through it on Wednesday night.

17:28.125 --> 17:32.068
How many of you would like to see that person six, eight months later, maybe up here,

17:32.048 --> 17:32.909
singing in the choir.

17:33.129 --> 17:35.372
How many of you think that might bring some joy to your heart?

17:36.994 --> 17:48.528
How many of you think that if they were so excited about Jesus and they started telling somebody about Jesus and they brought a friend to Jesus and you sat there one day and said, wow, I remember inviting them to come.

17:48.568 --> 17:49.770
Now they're inviting them to come.

17:49.970 --> 17:52.173
How many of you think that might be a blessing in your life?

17:53.154 --> 17:56.338
And so a part of our vision is just to remember our DNA.

17:57.186 --> 18:08.754
You know one of the challenges for a pastor, we've had a lot of vision, we've seen a lot of great things come to pass, but you know sometimes we need to get back to the very basic principles that brought God's blessing upon Lancaster Baptist Church.

18:08.930 --> 18:16.537
And the ministry path is nothing new, some new words, but it's the same biblical process that we've been following for 34 years.

18:16.937 --> 18:20.540
Now, what are some new things for the new year as we think about vision and where we're headed?

18:20.560 --> 18:22.282
Let me encourage you to turn to the next page.

18:22.302 --> 18:24.524
And I want to talk with you about just a few things.

18:24.564 --> 18:26.485
These are not all encompassing.

18:26.525 --> 18:27.786
These are just some highlights.

18:27.846 --> 18:28.667
There are many things.

18:29.047 --> 18:38.916
And if you looked at the calendar we passed out this morning, you should have seen many new events, many new service schedules that are brand new for 2020.

18:38.896 --> 18:41.789
you'll look at those and begin to mark your calendar accordingly.

18:42.251 --> 18:44.722
And here are some things we're going to be doing this year that

18:45.186 --> 18:50.170
I'll just kind of give you a little bit of the flavor for some of the opportunities that we have.

18:50.391 --> 18:52.472
We're excited about these coming up this April.

18:52.492 --> 18:56.015
We're gonna have a Sunday night service called Heart to Heart with Pastor Mrs. Chapel.

18:56.095 --> 18:57.737
Don't worry, Terry's not preaching, all right?

18:57.757 --> 18:58.498
Don't worry about that.

18:58.958 --> 19:15.172
But we're gonna have a special night where there will be preaching, but there's gonna be a time of question and answer, and we're gonna be taking some questions at a time about the ministry, about the church, about marriage, about whatever the church family's interested to know about, and we're gonna be having a heart to heart talk, just a great time of fellowship

19:15.152 --> 19:20.257
sharing and learning with our church family on April the 26th and September the 20th.

19:20.277 --> 19:31.970
We're having all church lunch and then an early evening service just looking at the calendar there at some busy seasons, lots of outreach, lots of special days and how we can have a time where we have our service.

19:32.551 --> 19:37.676
We have lunch on the grounds and then an early service and then head home, get some rest, get ready for the next week.

19:37.696 --> 19:40.759
Those are some new opportunities on the calendar.

19:41.160 --> 19:43.002
We're gonna have a great service on June the 7th.

19:43.022 --> 19:45.124
We're gonna call it memory lane evening service.

19:45.104 --> 19:47.266
And the Bible teaches us to remember.

19:47.306 --> 19:49.308
In fact, Terry and I were reading in our devotions.

19:49.329 --> 19:53.253
I think it was yesterday about remembering the days of old, David said.

19:53.313 --> 19:55.155
I think maybe Psalm 47.

19:55.555 --> 19:58.158
And he was praying out to God about the days of old.

19:58.178 --> 20:01.842
We're going to take some time and just remember some of the blessings of God.

20:02.302 --> 20:07.728
And I think sometimes as with David who said, you know, God allowed me to take down a bear and a lion.

20:07.748 --> 20:09.730
He's going to let me take down this Goliath too.

20:09.750 --> 20:12.814
And we're going to rejoice in some of the great things God has done.

20:13.054 --> 20:15.076
We have an outdoor evening service, July the 5th.

20:15.056 --> 20:19.100
We're going to have our spiritual leadership conference off campus this year.

20:19.140 --> 20:20.201
It's going to be quite different.

20:20.222 --> 20:24.226
It'll be held at a hotel convention center down in the Palm Desert area.

20:24.606 --> 20:27.229
And this will take place June 15th through 17th.

20:27.529 --> 20:31.333
That was something we did from the sense of looking for balance on the schedule.

20:31.694 --> 20:45.028
And because of the huge output of energy and finances and schedule for the spiritual leadership Asia conference, we're going to do a little less in the sense of energy and organizing here on our campus and try to give a bit of a

20:45.008 --> 20:48.494
and a respite, but we are going to have a great opportunity to minister.

20:48.534 --> 20:54.985
We already have a great number of pastors registered, and we'll be ministering to them in June, and we have many laymen from the churches coming.

20:55.025 --> 21:00.594
If you're interested in that, you can register tonight or anytime this week on the church website.

21:01.026 --> 21:02.968
July 12th, we're going to have food trucks out.

21:03.068 --> 21:06.110
We're going to have a great time of fellowship, a variety of different kinds of food.

21:06.511 --> 21:10.714
Back by popular demand is Aloha Sunday on August the 16th.

21:11.015 --> 21:11.675
What does that mean?

21:11.695 --> 21:14.438
It means I will preach in a hula shirt, I guess, if that's what they're called.

21:14.498 --> 21:14.878
I don't know.

21:15.559 --> 21:17.761
But this is one that we used to do years ago.

21:17.781 --> 21:20.743
We were talking with the staff about what are some fun things we can do.

21:21.204 --> 21:23.405
And I don't know if it's a hula shirt.

21:23.425 --> 21:24.406
I guess it's hula dresses.

21:24.446 --> 21:25.407
I won't wear one of those.

21:25.487 --> 21:31.012
But whatever they're called, a Hawaiian shirt, and just the time to kind of cool off a little bit and have

21:30.992 --> 21:32.954
some fun in the summertime.

21:33.335 --> 21:35.317
And I know that you'll look forward to that.

21:35.777 --> 21:38.800
And I was thinking, I'm still developing this one in my mind.

21:38.820 --> 21:45.768
I was thinking we might have the loudest Hawaiian shirt, you know, the ugliest Hawaiian, like the ugly Christmas sweater contest, something like that.

21:46.068 --> 21:47.730
But we'll work on that as we get closer.

21:48.250 --> 21:49.472
We have a great event planned.

21:49.492 --> 21:59.242
It's going to be hosted by the college, but all the church family will be welcome with Governor Mike Huckabee, who's just been a good conservative spokesperson in our country over the last many years.

21:59.903 --> 22:00.964
He's coming in to

22:00.944 --> 22:14.779
just help us in the ministry of West Coast Baptist College, but also an opportunity for our church to host a community event, an opportunity to share with our community, our values, our vision, why we reach young people and train young people for the gospel ministry.

22:15.079 --> 22:27.092
On November the 1st, we have a very special day called Decision Sunday, and just an opportunity to emphasize the importance of making decisions that keep us on track in our spiritual life.

22:27.112 --> 22:30.916
And so that's just a little sampling of some special days coming up

22:30.896 --> 22:33.939
in 2020 that I hope you will enjoy, that you'll grow through them.

22:34.180 --> 22:37.683
We'll talk about a few more events at the last part of this presentation.

22:38.024 --> 22:42.068
Let's turn right to the middle of the book and to our really big focus for 2020.

22:42.128 --> 22:46.032
This is something we've been talking about now for the last few years.

22:46.453 --> 22:52.619
And I believe we now have come to the year where we can begin construction on the Kid City project.

22:52.639 --> 22:53.800
Can I get an amen to that?

22:54.121 --> 22:56.183
It's something we've been praying about and looking forward to.

22:56.223 --> 22:58.365
I've been very patient.

22:58.425 --> 23:00.868
I've wanted our church to be ready for this.

23:00.848 --> 23:06.434
We've had a tremendous amount of study that has gone into the site, the necessary engineering.

23:06.994 --> 23:09.937
We've been involved in the city plan check for many, many months.

23:10.038 --> 23:11.960
All of that is finalizing now.

23:12.600 --> 23:25.874
Bids have gone out on the college portion of this for the college offices and shortly thereafter we'll get bids out, full sets of plans for the entire construction of the kid's city building.

23:25.922 --> 23:32.027
area of focus is our kid's city building, turning the entire north building into the kid's city building.

23:32.348 --> 23:35.410
And I believe that this really represents the future.

23:35.470 --> 23:37.372
I love the video we saw at the beginning of the service.

23:37.652 --> 23:40.795
When it talked about the future, it showed pictures of children.

23:41.115 --> 23:42.556
Children are the future.

23:42.657 --> 23:48.702
And how many of you are like me, you just kind of get amazed at how quickly they're growing and yet we're not getting any older.

23:48.742 --> 23:50.623
That just amazes me how that works.

23:50.704 --> 23:55.908
And spending some time with our grandkids this last week and looking at Camden, I mean almost as

23:55.888 --> 24:01.205
Paul is his mother Danielle and I just, I have trouble really getting my brain around those things sometimes.

24:01.526 --> 24:03.954
And you know, many of these children

24:04.002 --> 24:10.247
I believe are gonna be doing great things for the Lord, providing great leadership in the work of the Lord in the days ahead.

24:10.267 --> 24:16.713
But we wanna reach them while their hearts are tender, while they're reachable with the gospel of Jesus Christ.

24:16.773 --> 24:22.678
And so the first step for the Kids City Building will be the relocation of the college offices.

24:22.958 --> 24:25.761
How many of you have never been to the college offices?

24:25.781 --> 24:26.942
Let me see your hands, where are you?

24:27.182 --> 24:28.023
All right, lots of you.

24:28.303 --> 24:32.747
The second story of the North Building, the entire second story are college offices.

24:32.807 --> 24:33.988
It's kind of a labyrinth of office.

24:33.968 --> 24:40.961
offices or a bunch of them are in old closets and maintenance areas and it's really like little, you know, little pockets here and there.

24:41.362 --> 24:52.503
And so we're excited to provide nice sized offices and adequate space for about 70 college staff in the five modulars on the south end of the campus.

24:52.884 --> 24:54.226
And you see a picture there.

24:54.690 --> 24:58.098
on the right side of some of the work we'll do on the front of these buildings.

24:58.138 --> 25:06.056
But what's most important is the layout inside, the reception areas, the proper ventilation, the bathrooms that need to be built and all of these different things.

25:06.396 --> 25:07.699
And I would ask you to pray.

25:07.739 --> 25:08.882
Now we've been sharing

25:09.314 --> 25:15.379
with friends across the country and with alumni of the college and pastors and Christian businessmen about this need.

25:15.840 --> 25:18.182
And I don't have the exact bids in yet.

25:18.262 --> 25:23.386
The early preliminary prices were somewhere between 800,000 and a million dollars to relocate.

25:23.727 --> 25:32.234
And I'm not asking the church family to help with this, but I'm trying and asking folks that love the West Coast Baptist College ministry to help with this.

25:32.374 --> 25:38.159
I want our offerings 100% this year from Lancaster Baptist Church to go right into the kid's city building.

25:38.179 --> 25:39.300
But how many of you is your taking

25:39.280 --> 25:57.800
some notes tonight would just say, God, would you provide for the need of the college offices and for those letters pastor has sent, those people that he's talking to, would you touch some hearts so that the college offices can be transferred to the South Campus and that that can go smoothly in the early part of 2020?

25:57.860 --> 25:59.221
How many of you have prayed with me about that?

25:59.241 --> 26:00.122
Would you do that?

26:00.142 --> 26:01.203
I really appreciate that.

26:01.484 --> 26:09.252
Now, I don't have the exact amounts right up to this date, but so far we've had about $300,000 that has come in for that project.

26:09.232 --> 26:12.315
And we want to see the remaining amount of that come in by May.

26:12.395 --> 26:18.422
That's our graduation of the 25th graduating class of West Coast Baptist College, this May.

26:18.702 --> 26:22.006
And our big emphasis is on moving the college offices.

26:22.406 --> 26:28.352
And we hope, and my prayer is that we'll have a general contractor on site by March 1st.

26:28.392 --> 26:29.874
Now, mark this in your mind.

26:30.274 --> 26:39.204
When you see the contractors and their trucks and trailers beginning to work on the south end of that campus, you will know that the Kid City Project

26:39.184 --> 26:39.845
has begun.

26:40.166 --> 26:46.277
You say, but it's working at the south campus, but we've got to get that space there before we can start on the kid city building.

26:46.317 --> 26:55.533
So it's all going to flow together and we'll have some transition where some of the classes will be meeting in temporary space and it'll be a great time of growth.

26:55.553 --> 26:58.258
And we know that a growing church is always in

26:58.754 --> 26:59.395
transition.

26:59.475 --> 27:04.419
So be ready for some flexibility in the children's ministry as we get your new home ready.

27:04.919 --> 27:07.341
And we're very excited about getting that done.

27:07.662 --> 27:17.670
Now, now that we've come to the place where we have actual working drawings and we have a little better idea of timelines and budgets, it's very important that you understand the next couple of pages.

27:17.730 --> 27:22.935
And so I'd like you to turn to the next page there and you'll notice it says Kid City Showcase.

27:22.955 --> 27:28.740
And I want to share with you some things that are vitally important for all of us tonight to comprehend

27:28.720 --> 27:32.444
as we make way for the future at Lancaster Baptist Church.

27:32.744 --> 27:38.751
I want to show you on the right-hand side, first of all, where it says key dates, three things that I want you to remember.

27:38.791 --> 27:56.229
Number one, on February the 2nd, vision sharing Sunday, I'll be giving much more of an update as we'll have the working drawings, Lord willing, near completion or completed, and we'll be sharing in a full service opportunity where we're headed with the Kid City and the college offices.

27:56.710 --> 27:58.692
On February the 9th through the

27:58.672 --> 28:02.605
We're going to do something we've never done at Lancaster Baptist Church.

28:02.966 --> 28:06.879
We're going to be having what we're calling a kid city showcase.

28:07.340 --> 28:10.450
And this will take place on Sunday night, Monday night.

28:10.498 --> 28:11.880
Tuesday night and Wednesday night.

28:12.320 --> 28:23.676
There will be no regular Sunday night or Wednesday night service for that particular week because of the importance of having every adult member attend the Kid City Showcase.

28:23.696 --> 28:35.852
Now if you'll notice back on the left side it says about this showcase, it says, this completely unique walkthrough immersive experience will allow you to visualize and experience many of the best features of the new Kid City building.

28:36.332 --> 28:40.498
You will come into the Walther Center where you will meet your host for the evening

28:40.866 --> 28:44.889
We have been training 60 men from Lancaster Baptist Church.

28:45.350 --> 28:48.292
We're giving them the most up-to-date information on the budget.

28:48.813 --> 28:50.074
What have we raised thus far?

28:50.174 --> 28:55.359
How much funds are available after the completion of the Elden Loft and Transportation facility?

28:55.959 --> 29:01.244
We're teaching them also about lots of the specs of the building and information related to the building.

29:01.264 --> 29:04.647
They'll have all of the up-to-date information on the project.

29:04.667 --> 29:07.149
They'll also be asking you for any questions you might have.

29:07.409 --> 29:10.852
They'll be sharing with you lots of information in visual form.

29:10.832 --> 29:12.213
And so you'll meet your hosts.

29:12.474 --> 29:21.944
There'll be a time while we're waiting for everyone to get there to meet and discuss and hear the testimony of your host and fellowship with some of your friends from Lancaster Baptist Church.

29:21.964 --> 29:32.215
Then your group of a size maybe 10 to 12 adults will be guided through six amazing life size displays highlighting the feature of the Kids City building.

29:32.595 --> 29:40.043
We have a great team of people right now working to create for us an identity and understanding of this building.

29:40.083 --> 29:40.804
In fact, when you get

29:40.784 --> 29:50.735
to the very end of this display, you will be the very first to see the famous slide of the Kid City Building, but you will not be able to slide down the slide, all right?

29:51.055 --> 29:54.439
I'm sorry to hurt your heart there, but it won't be properly attached just yet.

29:55.019 --> 30:01.326
But you'll receive a detailed brochure on the building with floor plans and timelines, have an opportunity to ask questions, to give input.

30:01.806 --> 30:10.756
If anything, this is just gonna be a great time of fellowship, a great time of information, a great time to meet some new friends, and I've already had

30:10.736 --> 30:21.347
We had way back in December, the first meeting with the first 60 men and begun to share with them the heart, how much I appreciate their involvement in conveying the vision and helping.

30:21.768 --> 30:24.471
In the past, we've gone to homes and shared the vision.

30:24.571 --> 30:27.774
We've had dinners six, eight nights in a row.

30:28.115 --> 30:34.461
This year, this immersive experience will be something for every adult member of Lancaster Baptist Church.

30:34.541 --> 30:40.708
Now, this is an illustration, as we said a moment ago, about enjoying serving the Lord at Lancaster Baptist

30:40.688 --> 30:42.550
the pace of our schedule.

30:42.850 --> 30:54.863
And so rather than have you out on a Sunday night and then a Monday night or a Sunday night and a Tuesday night, we're gonna ask you to look at your calendar and figure out the night that's best for you, Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday.

30:55.244 --> 31:00.669
Furthermore, you're going to have opportunity to choose a time slot, 6.30, seven o'clock, 7.15.

31:00.729 --> 31:10.660
And on each of those nights, we're going to have between 20 and 30 groups going through this experience, enjoying the visual display,

31:10.640 --> 31:23.814
seeing a presentation that I will give as well, and then moving on into the Walther Center for some refreshments, a time of understanding from your host, a time of Q and A, and most of all, a time of prayer.

31:24.275 --> 31:37.809
Now our opportunity to get this building built is upon us, and there are some very unique facets to this year's opportunity, never done before at Lancaster Baptist Church, that they will explain to you in great detail that night.

31:38.129 --> 31:40.612
But perhaps the most significant aspect that

31:40.592 --> 31:46.038
that they'll share with you is going to be for the first time ever our 24 month commitment.

31:46.078 --> 31:55.808
We're going to ask our church family this year to not only give our best cash offering as we attempt to do every year, but then to make a 24 month commitment.

31:55.868 --> 32:04.678
So someone might give a cash offering this March and a commitment for 12 months and then another cash offering the next March, but there will be no presentation.

32:04.718 --> 32:06.800
There will be no immersive experience.

32:06.820 --> 32:09.483
There will be no presentations of that type next year.

32:09.563 --> 32:10.564
We're doing all of that.

32:10.544 --> 32:14.070
this year and then we're going to make our commitment.

32:14.110 --> 32:16.114
We'll give our cash offering and make our commitment.

32:16.494 --> 32:18.758
It will extend for a 24 month period.

32:18.778 --> 32:21.803
Someone might give one cash offering and 24 month commitment.

32:22.044 --> 32:24.328
Somebody might want to give a couple of times a cash offering.

32:24.588 --> 32:25.590
That will be up to you.

32:25.890 --> 32:29.557
The following year we'll have something like a reminder Sunday or something like that.

32:29.957 --> 32:35.026
Now I'm going to tell you one of the reasons why we're going to share this new schedule with you.

32:35.458 --> 32:56.456
That is very simply, as we're coming into this very large project of the kid's city building, historically over the years I have been involved in working with our building committee and bearing under the pressure of a building construction program while at the same time trying to continually oversee a stewardship campaign.

32:56.817 --> 33:04.283
I've told you in the past, some churches hire an outside company to come in and do the immersive experience and even bring speakers in to motivate.

33:04.463 --> 33:05.444
And I've just felt like this

33:05.424 --> 33:06.147
this over the years.

33:06.508 --> 33:09.539
I don't want to give 10% of our offering to an outside company.

33:11.165 --> 33:14.376
I want everything that comes in for this building to go right to the building, amen.

33:15.761 --> 33:17.106
But in order to

33:17.154 --> 33:24.140
oversee and help with construction and also be involved in the stewardship campaign and also pastor the church and do everything else.

33:24.440 --> 33:27.423
You're kind of spinning a lot of plates and it's taking a lot of energy.

33:27.443 --> 33:34.069
And I really look forward to having a 24 month commitment so that we'll take care of the stewardship component in 2020.

33:34.789 --> 33:40.774
And in 2021, we can focus on getting the building finished and built to the glory of God.

33:41.135 --> 33:43.797
And we'll talk about where we are with our commitments and things like that.

33:44.117 --> 33:47.140
But for the first time, you'll hear about the 24 month commitment.

33:47.120 --> 33:50.023
how we can make that commitment and how that will work.

33:50.303 --> 34:02.597
And this will enable us to say to the contractors, look, we have this much money on hand and we know that if the project starts late 2020 and goes somewhat into 2021, we've already received the commitment from our church family.

34:02.837 --> 34:04.098
Go get to work.

34:04.118 --> 34:05.119
We're serious.

34:05.139 --> 34:06.561
We want to get this building done.

34:06.601 --> 34:08.162
How many of you understand the concept of that?

34:08.203 --> 34:11.346
Isn't that a tremendous blessing to be able to say, let's get it done.

34:11.626 --> 34:12.607
We've made the commitment.

34:12.827 --> 34:14.229
And so that's going to be explained.

34:14.269 --> 34:16.311
How does the 24 month commitment work?

34:16.331 --> 34:17.092
And so we'll have it.

34:17.072 --> 34:23.259
to showcase the opportunity to see the building, to see the timeline, to see how we can get it funded for the glory of God.

34:23.599 --> 34:26.282
And that will then lead us into March the first.

34:26.302 --> 34:29.625
March the first is our reaching forth offering and banquet.

34:30.006 --> 34:32.488
On that night, we're gonna have a great time of worship.

34:32.508 --> 34:33.369
We're gonna come together.

34:33.710 --> 34:35.011
It's not gonna be a long message.

34:35.031 --> 34:36.172
I'll be preaching that night.

34:36.653 --> 34:39.916
We've invited a tremendous singing quartet, the amen quartet to come in.

34:40.237 --> 34:42.960
And they're gonna put on a gospel concert while the offering's being counted.

34:43.200 --> 34:47.044
And we're gonna enjoy hearing them as well as some of our ensembles and children's choirs.

34:47.024 --> 34:48.065
It's gonna be a wonderful night.

34:48.385 --> 34:52.670
And on that night, we're praying that we'll be able to take a very special offering.

34:53.010 --> 35:12.772
I'm asking the Lord for the largest offering in the history of our church along with tremendous commitments and that with those commitments and offering, we'll be able to take the contract or have a meeting, sign the contract and be ready just as soon as those offices are moved out and as soon as the plans are given to us and we have approval to get started on the Kid City Building.

35:13.092 --> 35:14.253
And I don't know the exact time.

35:14.293 --> 35:16.996
I think it'll be later on in 2020.

35:16.976 --> 35:25.053
Tonight would say, Pastor, I will pray with you that that kid's building gets started this year to the glory of God.

35:25.073 --> 35:26.235
How many of you will pray with me about that?

35:26.736 --> 35:28.300
I really believe this is the time.

35:28.680 --> 35:34.853
I've kind of been holding back, waiting for the right time, waiting to see the plans, get ready, and we have to have those approved by the city.

35:34.873 --> 35:37.138
Everything's beginning to come together.

35:37.218 --> 35:46.486
college office component is very large and I again covet your purse for that but as soon as we can see that out and going we're going to get moving forward on the Kid City building.

35:46.686 --> 35:53.712
So please mark those dates down February the 2nd is a vision sharing Sunday February 9th, 10th, 11th, 12th Kid City showcase.

35:53.752 --> 36:07.204
Now what we want to encourage you to do tonight after the service at every exit there are signup tables where you can go and make your appointment and so I want you to say all right I'd like to come Sunday night at five because that's already

36:07.184 --> 36:12.490
part of my schedule, or I'd like to come Monday night at six and get that scheduled.

36:12.510 --> 36:16.174
When you make that reservation, you'll receive a reaching fourth pin.

36:16.794 --> 36:19.377
There's no cost to attend this event.

36:19.397 --> 36:21.139
It's just the commitment of being there.

36:21.459 --> 36:26.665
We've got some men who have taken off time from work, and they're not going to come for one night.

36:26.685 --> 36:31.950
They're going to come for four or five nights in order to facilitate this opportunity for us.

36:31.991 --> 36:33.873
Some of them are helping with the Spanish as well.

36:34.313 --> 36:37.156
And so we want to be honoring their schedule by making

36:37.136 --> 36:42.061
appointment, keeping our appointment, and you can make your appointment tonight at all these doors on your way out.

36:42.302 --> 36:45.165
Be sure to sign up and be a part of Kids City Showcase.

36:45.405 --> 36:50.510
You also can go online on the Lancaster Baptist app and register that way as well.

36:50.831 --> 37:01.362
But we want you to know what's happening and know how to be a part of this new opportunity for the 24 month commitment and how to pray for a great victory on that special day, March the 1st.

37:01.442 --> 37:03.604
And so that's the big project.

37:03.624 --> 37:05.206
You say what's different from last year.

37:05.446 --> 37:07.108
The big difference is what I said a moment ago.

37:07.088 --> 37:09.651
We're praying to start the project this year.

37:09.931 --> 37:11.773
Last year we were revving up, getting ready.

37:12.093 --> 37:16.657
This year we're still getting ready with the offering this March, but we want to see the project begin.

37:16.918 --> 37:18.139
And it's going to be an exciting time.

37:18.159 --> 37:23.644
We're going to have to take dozens of classes out of the North Building, relocate them to modulars, possibly bring some other space in.

37:24.025 --> 37:27.128
It's going to be a great time though, to get it all done for the glory of God.

37:27.148 --> 37:33.554
And I've been saying this for several years now, but we have visitors who have been giving us comments.

37:33.602 --> 37:38.387
biggest negatives that we get is how spread out all the children's classes are.

37:38.468 --> 37:41.831
And so we're very anxious to centralize those classes.

37:42.092 --> 37:45.055
And we want the kids to love everything about Kid City.

37:45.075 --> 37:48.759
The lessons, the songs, the slide, the puppet shows, all of it.

37:49.000 --> 37:52.163
We want them dragging their parents back to church the next Sunday.

37:52.444 --> 37:54.125
We want them bringing the whole family in.

37:54.145 --> 37:56.088
So you pray for the Kid City project.

37:56.308 --> 37:58.130
Let's turn to the next page for just a moment.

37:58.530 --> 38:00.552
I want to share just some high-end goals.

38:00.932 --> 38:05.776
Every department has numerous dozens of goals, but just to share some things with you church-wide.

38:06.097 --> 38:09.179
We're excited this fall about reinstituting our Love Works campaign.

38:09.439 --> 38:13.503
We want to have five major Love Works opportunities this fall.

38:13.523 --> 38:26.474
Love Works, for those of you that haven't been a part of it, that's when we buy 1,000 cups of coffee and go to the commuter parking lots and give out cups of coffee at 4.30 in the morning along with the gospel track and tell people that God loves them and so does Lancaster Baptist Church.

38:26.795 --> 38:28.516
I think one of the things we did before we painted

38:28.496 --> 38:58.468
veterans building and we've had people coming to church every week since that just because we went painted a building passed out some gospel tracks and love people in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ our youth ministry they went out to some public high schools and they serve spaghetti to football teams and basketball teams and and preach the gospel right in those basketball gymnasiums and saw souls saved so you'll be hearing about love works this fall five major opportunities you'll have to sign up to be a part of reaching our community with the gospel we want to be

38:58.448 --> 39:02.292
We want to begin the construction of the college offices this spring.

39:03.513 --> 39:04.974
This spring, we want to get that done.

39:05.015 --> 39:07.877
So mark that down as a major prayer request.

39:08.118 --> 39:11.721
We want to begin the construction of the kid's city building in the winter.

39:13.183 --> 39:13.523
All right.

39:13.543 --> 39:14.284
That's a little weak.

39:14.304 --> 39:16.346
That's sort of like a Methodist church with a lady pastor.

39:16.366 --> 39:17.587
