51:53.328 --> 52:04.960
and I don't have one, but I nearly always have my phone and I've got that app, and I've witnessed to several people on it, want to encourage you, this is a church that believes in equipping the saints for the work of the ministry.

52:04.980 --> 52:08.624
Let's say that together, equipping the saints for the work of the ministry.

52:08.845 --> 52:10.086
What's pastor doing right now?

52:10.406 --> 52:15.712
I'm trying to equip you and give you some tools so that you can be involved in the work of the ministry.

52:15.732 --> 52:23.300
So the devotionals are in the back there, the daily vibrating schedules, they're available for you in the back, and I hope you'll take some time and just kind

52:23.280 --> 52:33.238
to kind of get geared up for the year and with some of these things that will remind you and keep you involved in a devotional life and in a soul winning life as well.

52:33.258 --> 52:36.564
Now as we continue along just real quickly I want you to turn to the next page.

52:36.804 --> 52:39.109
Where are we headed in our preaching and teaching this year?

52:39.569 --> 52:44.338
And we started this morning a brand new series entitled Let the Journey Begin.

52:44.802 --> 52:47.404
And we're learning about how to reach forth.

52:47.805 --> 52:54.671
And next week I'll be preaching on reaching forth with focus and our focus on Jesus Christ from Hebrews chapter 12.

52:55.011 --> 52:56.612
And I'm very excited about this series.

52:57.013 --> 53:05.200
Every week we'll be talking about some part of the Christian life that God specifically tells us to be looking to or reaching for or seeking.

53:05.500 --> 53:11.885
And so reaching forth is our preaching theme for the first quarter on Sunday morning as the journey has begun.

53:12.226 --> 53:14.788
And then beginning on Sunday evenings we're going to be

53:14.768 --> 53:20.334
coming back to the book of Philippians and we're going to be looking at some highlight passages from Philippians.

53:20.394 --> 53:26.541
For example, next Sunday night I'll be preaching on the confidence of the Christian life from Philippians chapter one.

53:26.621 --> 53:34.950
Paul said being confident of this very thing that he which hath begun a good work will continue and perform it in you until the day of Jesus Christ.

53:35.230 --> 53:42.918
And we're going to be learning from the Philippians this Sunday night beginning this next Sunday night for the next 10 to 12 Sundays.

53:43.098 --> 53:44.740
And then on Wednesday nights I'm very excited

53:44.720 --> 53:47.723
You know, as a pastor, I really do spend time in prayer.

53:47.803 --> 53:51.346
Lord, where do we need to emphasize and what do we need to emphasize?

53:51.366 --> 53:59.773
And sometimes I get this burden and all I want to preach about is the family, marriage and raising kids because you do a lot of counseling, you hear about problems and you want to preach just about the family.

54:00.074 --> 54:12.244
And other times all I want to do is preach on prophecy because I think, boy, the Lord's coming soon and we need to understand what's going on over there in the Middle East and how does it relate to what scripture and so all these things and all these problems you want to preach about.

54:12.485 --> 54:14.066
And then there's this thought too.

54:14.114 --> 54:21.360
And I think, you know, Lord, I've been preaching for 34 years now at Lancaster Baptist, but there are some books I haven't preached through yet.

54:21.721 --> 54:25.544
I've preached through about 30, maybe 35, but there's 66 of them.

54:25.944 --> 54:28.406
And so I feel like I've got to get going here.

54:28.587 --> 54:30.188
I've been a slacker.

54:30.248 --> 54:31.889
I haven't preached through enough books of the Bible.

54:32.310 --> 54:44.100
And so this year on Wednesday nights for the next, I think about, oh, I don't know how many it is, 12, 14, we're gonna take the next several months and we're gonna be going through the profit

54:44.080 --> 54:45.362
of the Old Testament.

54:45.402 --> 54:47.886
I've entitled this series, The Lord Have Spoken.

54:48.326 --> 54:49.168
The Lord Have Spoken.

54:49.588 --> 54:55.877
And we're not going to be able to go through the entire book of Isaiah, for example, but here's what we're going to do with a book like Isaiah.

54:55.937 --> 55:00.164
It might take two or three weeks, but we're going to start this Wednesday night with Obadiah.

55:00.544 --> 55:07.154
We're going to look at some of the minor prophets and some of the major prophets and endeavor to familiarize our church family

55:07.202 --> 55:28.500
with every book of the Bible beginning with these major and minor prophets so that you'll be able to understand what is the context of Obadiah, what year was it written, and what was going on in the history of Israel and was the divided kingdom or the United Kingdom and who was the king and what is the major teaching of that book so that you'll have an overview and an understanding of the major and minor prophets.

55:28.520 --> 55:32.464
And I've asked some of our teaching staff and leadership team to join me in this process.

55:32.684 --> 55:37.188
Dr. Lester will be teaching this Wednesday night on Obadiah and I'm just saying many

55:37.168 --> 55:44.115
not here have ever heard preaching from the book of Obadiah to understand the context of that book, for example.

55:44.356 --> 55:46.938
And I want our church to know the word and study the word.

55:46.999 --> 55:49.401
So I'm excited about this series on Wednesday night.

55:49.601 --> 55:54.887
The Lord has spoken, getting an overview on the prophets of the Old Testament.

55:54.907 --> 56:01.534
And so we'll be in Philippians on Sunday night, the prophets on Wednesday night, Sunday morning, learning how to reach forth in the Christian life.

56:01.874 --> 56:07.140
And how many of you say, Pastor, I'm gonna pray for you as you prepare these messages and feed the flock of God.

56:07.120 --> 56:09.523
God that we might grow stronger in our faith this year.

56:09.543 --> 56:10.063
Will you do that?

56:10.404 --> 56:12.546
That's my desire that we might truly grow.

56:12.806 --> 56:14.008
Let's look at the next page here.

56:14.308 --> 56:16.230
It talks about the week of awakening.

56:16.371 --> 56:21.156
I love the video this morning that we saw with the quotes from revivalists of the past.

56:21.536 --> 56:24.640
We all know the greatest need in our life is revival.

56:25.100 --> 56:27.043
The greatest need in our nation is revival.

56:27.543 --> 56:30.306
And I want to ask our church to take this to heart.

56:31.408 --> 56:37.074
I believe that being thoroughly right with God takes care of so many other things.

56:38.050 --> 56:38.991
It brings unity.

56:39.832 --> 56:41.553
It takes away bitterness.

56:42.895 --> 56:45.197
I pray for every age group in our church.

56:45.257 --> 56:51.082
And I pray for the teenagers, because sometimes the devil tries to get them to be rebellious against their parents.

56:51.122 --> 56:58.489
And then I pray for millennials, because sometimes the young couples in the church, they can say, I've been there, done that, and that looks cool.

56:58.569 --> 57:01.812
And get more into materialism and less interested in spiritual things.

57:01.832 --> 57:02.593
And I just pray.

57:02.993 --> 57:04.234
Sometimes I don't know what to say.

57:04.295 --> 57:08.018
Sometimes I'll write a note or ask a teacher how someone's doing.

57:08.130 --> 57:10.132
I try to pray for the young couples.

57:10.172 --> 57:14.757
I pray for the older couples, some that have health problems and all the different needs of the church.

57:14.837 --> 57:17.020
There are so many needs in a church like ours.

57:17.961 --> 57:19.702
And frankly, sometimes it's overwhelming.

57:20.403 --> 57:23.827
Just all the different things that are needed spiritually.

57:24.608 --> 57:28.672
But there's one thing that can meet all the other needs.

57:29.373 --> 57:32.256
And that is every one of us being thoroughly right with God.

57:33.257 --> 57:35.359
Every one of us having revival.

57:35.479 --> 57:37.842
And that's why we have this revival meeting.

57:37.954 --> 57:40.303
I think you've kind of got my heart by now.

57:40.625 --> 57:45.785
If I thought it was just something on the calendar, just some busy thing, we would have canceled it.

57:46.769 --> 57:49.138
I don't think it's just something on the calendar.

57:49.218 --> 57:50.079
to keep us busy.

